    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-07-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-07-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="191" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Butler</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reply of Mexican Government regarding Rowes not yet received. Have
                            ascertained, however, that extradition Chester will be refused upon the
                            ground of his Mexican nationality, but he will be tried here for stolen
                            funds. Richard will be held pending the arrival of extradition papers.
                            This result in despite of presentation your cabled opinion of the 19th.
                            Can you urge extradition Chester through Mexican minister at
                            Washington?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Butler.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
